Description: Year 9 Social Studies is derived from the Social Sciences learning area of the NZC and aims to enable students to participate in a changing society as informed, confident and responsible citizens. Students’ learning is based around four conceptual strands: Identity, Culture and Organisation, Place and Environment, Continuity and Change, The Economic World. This provides a foundation for the separate Social Science disciplines offered in the senior secondary school.Topics include:-identity, Local Histrory, Human Rights and Sustainable Devlepoment Goals.

Name: Digital Technologies
Description: NCEA Level 1 Digital Technology achievement standards will enable students to develop skills and knowledge of tools and techniques in three areas: Design  - Throughout the year students will learn about design and how to apply these principles to their work.Programming - Students will learn problem-solving and programming skills to develop an algorithm & create a computer program using Python.Digital Outcome - Students will implement basic procedures to produce a professional digital outcome through coding a website using HTML and CSS and integrating other media such as photos, animation & 3D modelling. Students gain 15 NCEA Level 1 Credits through Internal and External achievement standards and develop the skills required for excellence endorsement at Level 1. You can gain (A.M.E) endorsement. Further assessment opportunities are not available in this course.

Name: Digital Technologies
Description: NCEA Level 2 Digital Technology achievement standards will enable students to develop skills and knowledge of tools and techniques in three areas:  Digital Media - Web - Students will develop a digital media outcome based in the web field.Programming - Students will learn problem-solving and programming skills to develop an algorithm & create a computer program using Python.Digital Outcome Process - Students will implement an agile process cycle to produce a professional digital outcome through coding a website using HTML and CSS and integrating other media such as photos, animation & 3D modelling. This will prepare them for the external assessment requirements.You can gain (A.M.E) endorsement. Further assessment opportunities are not available in this course.

Name: Digital Technologies
Description: NCEA Level 3 Digital Technology achievement standards will enable students to develop skills and knowledge of tools and techniques in three areas:  Digital Outcome Process - Students will implement an agile process cycle to produce a professional digital outcome through coding a website using HTML and CSS and integrating other media such as photos, animation & 3D modelling. This will prepare them for the external assessment requirements.Digital Media - Web - Students will develop a digital media outcome based in the web field.Programming - Students will learn problem-solving and programming skills to develop an algorithm & create a computer program using Python.You can gain (A.M.E) endorsement and UE with 14 or more credits. Further assessment opportunities are not available in this course.

Name: Design & Visual Communication
Description: Course description:The successful completion of this course will give students an understanding of the design process, sketching and rendering techniques, instrumental drawing knowledge in the areas of both spatial (architecture) and product design. Students will work on up to two folios of work that will be assessed both internally and externally. Some independent work outside of class is expected.Course objectives:Students gain up to 15 NCEA Level 1 Credits through Internal and External achievement standards and develop the skills required for excellence endorsement at Level 1.

Name: Design & Visual Communication
Description: Course description:Students will work on up to two folios of work that will be assessed both internally and externally. Students work on two projects. One will be spatial (architecture) based and the other product based. Student work is shaped by a teacher given brief.Course objectives:Students gain up to 18 NCEA Level 2 Credits.

Name: Explore Emergency Services Level 1 Whenua Iti
Financial Planning & Literacy
Description: Financial planning and literacy will give students the knowledge and skills to manage money andmake informed financial decisions. Financial security in adulthood is important, and this course willhelp students understand how to plan for their futures. Learning activities will include hands-ontasks and some written work.
